And with his Chakra he created that Chakrapushkarni, Manikarnika Kund, and that Kund is filled with the sweat of Lord Vishnu.

39
00:03:55,208 --> 00:04:03,375
So when Mother Parvati and Lord Shankar came for a visit, they saw that there was a pond here, but there was nothing in it.

40
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:13,416
So when Lord Shankar and Mother Parvati go to meditate, then Lord Shankar's gem falls, and along with it the earring of Mother Parvati also fell.

41
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:26,041
When they started searching and did not find it, then Lord Vishnu says, it is cursed, keep something here which will make a big place in the belief of Hindu religion.

42
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:33,916
Which is the biggest pilgrimage site among the pilgrimage sites, then Lord Shankar named it Manikarnika Ghat.

43
00:04:35,416 --> 00:04:41,458
Mani-Karnika and Ghat, then the name of Chakrapushkarni changed to Manikarnika.

44
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:45,875
So whenever any pilgrimage site comes here, the biggest pilgrimage is Manikarnika.

45
00:04:46,291 --> 00:04:52,375
